    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "just to expand on the issue linked above:\r\n\r\n> It looks like you are either using mac, or some platform with libusb. In that case, acquiring a meaningful error message is not implemented yet.\r\n\r\nSince we use libusb as a backend for `ethers-rs`, we cannot take his suggestion to use `hidraw`\r\n\r\nHowever, this \"only\" limits us getting a valid/verbose USB error (from my understanding). Are you able to use your ledger otherwise? Is it possible that the device is locked or taken by another process when you try to call forge or cast with it ?",
